# 10cc1531d8c1451e92ee48aada738517
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:4
msgid "Balancer Plugin"
msgstr ""

# fb0e932d2ff54637af6acb4bdd0e84d6
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:24
msgid ""
"The ``balancer`` balances requests across multiple origin servers. To use"
" this plugin, configure it in a :file:`remap.config` rule, specifying a "
"balancing policy and a set of origin servers. For example::"
msgstr ""

# edb1517cd60d444b8a110145f53a5151
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:31
msgid ""
"The ``replacement`` URL in the mapping rule is not used. The argument to "
"the ``--policy`` option is a comma-separated list of keywords. The first "
"keyword is the name of a balancing policy. The subsequent keywords are "
"used to refine the requested policy."
msgstr ""

# 76039fcbed1d4ae49aabf4490f163d9a
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:36
msgid ""
"The remaining plugin arguments are balancer targets. Typically, these "
"will be the host names of origin servers that requests should be balanced"
" across. The target name may contain a colon-separated port number."
msgstr ""

# 715868ea3c584b73b75d6e4c9171ac0a
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:42
msgid "Hash Balancing Policy"
msgstr ""

# a5685751d5534a1fa4dd0813a8efcc1f
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:44
msgid ""
"The ``hash`` balancing policy performs a consistent hash across the set "
"of origins. This minimizes the number of hash entries that must be moved "
"when the set of origin servers changes. An optional list of hash fields "
"follows the ``hash`` keyword. Each specified hash field is hashed to "
"select an outbound origin server."
msgstr ""

# f3128138f4fd4cbfbc1dc8ab58482a23
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:50
msgid "The following fields can be supplied to the hash:"
msgstr ""

# ee5553c93da24a81b3c2bae44d3c736b
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:55
msgid "key"
msgstr ""

# 96b4a800ff0945c1a55bcdbfb8863682
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:53
msgid ""
"The request cache key. Note that the cache key will only be set if you "
"have already chained a plugin that sets a custom cache key."
msgstr ""

# 4f350f9cc4fb4685969e77926056d7d6
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:59
msgid "url"
msgstr ""

# 2f0fd7982eca4ca193a9eea12662a19c
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:58
msgid ""
"The request URL. This is the default hash field that is used if no other "
"fields are specified."
msgstr ""

# fe65553f2bcd46408aa220edd00b349e
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:62
msgid "srcaddr"
msgstr ""

# 9f2bf693402f41c7a95c6ce0cd38f042
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:62
msgid "The source IP address of the request."
msgstr ""

# c3651e91aa5743dbb2a68a201a8c24d2
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:65
msgid "dstaddr"
msgstr ""

# 293ac595c1754c298f2212a27f428e5d
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:65
msgid "The destination IP address of the request."
msgstr ""

# 8b91f5f209c54279b34877bf140632b2
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:68
msgid "Round Robin Balancing Policy"
msgstr ""

# 4b3ad4fee2654bce90a01c1b84a80f81
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:70
msgid ""
"The ``roundrobin`` balancing policy simply allocates requests to origin "
"servers in order. Over time, the number of requests received by each "
"origin should be approximately the same."
msgstr ""

# fd2b0888aa3f408db807aa0dc8a5ad7a
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:75
msgid "Health Checking"
msgstr ""

# ec7721d9966f4365a1f3e34bde8f3850
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/balancer.en.rst:77
msgid ""
"The ``balancer`` plugin does not check the health of the origin servers, "
"however the plugin is fully reloadable so health checking is usualy "
"simple to implement. Most production environments already have mechanisms"
" to check service health. It is recommended that you write a simple "
"script to monitor this information and rewrite :file:`remap.config` when "
"appropriate. Running :option:`traffic_ctl config reload` will reload the "
"``balancer`` plugin with the new set of origin servers."
msgstr ""

